    <h2>Route 57 ñ Proposed Flex Route</h2>
    
    <p align="center"><img src="/img/MapFlex57.jpg" width="650" height="1093" alt="Proposed Flex Route" /></p>
    	
    <p>The proposed flex route provides the reliability of a fixed route schedule with the convenience of curb-to-curb service, for paratransit eligible riders, to requested deviations within a 3/4 mile zone of the route. Deviation requests must be scheduled in advance via phone and are limited to one deviation per trip to maintain the fixed route schedule. The proposed flex route also provides an additional transit option for customers making paratransit trips within the 3/4 mile zone. </p>
	
	<h3>Route</h3>
	
        <ul>
        <li>60 minute weekday frequency</li>
        <li>13 hour service span from 6:00 AM to 7:30 PM</li>
        <li>16 revenue trips / 12 revenue hours</li>
        <li>Service to operate in conventional fixed-route, fixed-schedule mode, with one deviation per trip.<strong> Deviations are for Paratransit customers only</strong>. Deviations to occur up to æ mile within the demand responsive zone. </li>
        <li>Coordination with fixed-route service at Main and Niagara and at the Niagara Falls International Airport will be established to ensure seamless transfer to and from the flex-route service. </li>
        </ul>
    <h3>Fare</h3>
        <ul>
        <li>Regular fare for customers boarding at a bus stop along the regular route, current fare is $2, with no charge to Paratransit eligible passengers. </li>
        <li>No additional fare for deviations </li>
        <li>Deviation reservations will require a 24 hour advance notice </li>
        </ul>
